// MARKDOWNFUNC: Block
// CONTEXT: %s
// Attacker writes a single backslash before [^name] in an attempt to make
// the escape Block adds collapse into a literal `\\` pair, leaving the
// `[^name]` invocation unescaped. The byte-walk parity rule prepends an
// extra backslash so the total count stays odd; the rendered HTML must
// NOT contain a footnote-ref. See CommonMark §2.4.
-- input.md --
\[^realm-footnote]
-- output.md --
\\\[^realm-footnote]
-- output.html --
<p>\[^realm-footnote]</p>
